originalText: Target wall can now attack. Target wall's power and toughness are unchanged, even if its power is 0.

text: Enchant Wall\nEnchanted Wall can attack as though it didn't have defender.

name: Armageddon
originalText: All lands in play are destroyed.
printings: 2ED, 30A, 3ED, 4BB, 4ED, 5ED, 6ED, A25, ATH, CED, CEI, FBB, G04, LEA, LEB, ME1, ME4, MP2, P02, POR, PRM, PTC, S99, SUM, V14, VMA, WC00, WC98
text: Destroy all lands.

name: Balance
originalText: Whichever player has more lands in play must discard enough lands of his or her choice to equalize the number of lands both players have in play. Cards in hand and creatures in play must be equalized the same way. Creatures lost in this manner may not be regenerated.
printings: 2ED, 30A, 3ED, 4BB, 4ED, CED, CEI, EMA, FBB, G04, LEA, LEB, ME4, OLEP, PRM, PTC, SLD, SUM, V09, VMA
text: Each player chooses a number of lands they control equal to the number of lands controlled by the player who controls the fewest, then sacrifices the rest. Players discard cards and sacrifice creatures the same way.

flavorText: Benalia has a complex caste system that changes with the lunar year. No matter what the season, the only caste that cannot be attained by either heredity or money is that of the hero.
name: Benalish Hero
originalText: Bands
printings: 2ED, 30A, 3ED, 4BB, 4ED, 5ED, CED, CEI, FBB, LEA, LEB, ME1, SUM
text: Banding (Any creatures with banding, and up to one without, can attack in a band. Bands are blocked as a group. If any creatures with banding you control are blocking or being blocked by a creature, you divide that creature's combat damage, not its controller, among any of the creatures it's being blocked by or is blocking.)

name: Black Ward
originalText: Target creature gains protection from black.
printings: 2ED, 30A, 3ED, 4BB, 4ED, CED, CEI, FBB, LEA, LEB, SUM
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature has protection from black. This effect doesn't remove Black Ward.

name: Blaze of Glory
originalText: Target defending creature can and must block all attacking creatures it can legally block. For example, a normal non-flying target defender can and must block all normal non-flying attackers at once, but it cannot block any flying attackers. Controller of target defender may distribute damage among attackers as desired. Play before defense is chosen.
text: Cast this spell only during combat before blockers are declared.\nTarget creature defending player controls can block any number of creatures this turn. It blocks each attacking creature this turn if able.

originalText: oo\nW Target creature gains +1/+1 until end of turn.

originalText: o1: Prevents all damage against you from one black source. If a source does damage to you more than once in a turn, you must pay 1 mana each time to prevent the damage.
